main event: A photograph taken in Switzerland in 1959 possibly shows an unidentified object, which was later analyzed and deemed to likely be a reflection.
interesting points: The photograph taken in Switzerland is a copy and the original source couldn't be identified,The analysis concluded that the oblong streak in the photo is probably due to reflection,The report includes an account of bright flashes and a cigar-shaped object seen in the sky,The photograph has been associated with a later analysis that supported its inconclusiveness,The photograph was submitted by Miss Dora Bauer and taken by Franz Hlawa at a high altitude.
sighted object: an oblong, possibly unidentified flying object
witness description: nobody in the party saw the object; it appeared only on the film
